    schema:author "Connie Willis" ;
    schema:dateCreated "2013"^^xsd:int ;
    schema:genre hpcom:BookFiction,
        hpcom:BookSciFi ;
    schema:name "Time is the Fire: The Best of Connie Willis" ;
    schema:review "An excellent collection of short stories that really show the breadth and versatility and quality of Connie Willis in being one of the reknowned writers. Enjoyable collection, even though a lot of them are not hard sci-fi. The background and explanations following the stories also made for an intersting read in to the origins of the stories."@en ;
    schema:url "https://harshp.com/hobbies/books/628"^^xsd:anyURI .

book:629 a hpcom:Book,
        hpcom:BookReading,
        hpcom:RenderedItem,
        schema:Book ;
    hpcom:book_id hpcom:629 ;
    hpcom:book_owned_medium hpcom:EBook ;
    hpcom:book_read_medium hpcom:EBook ;
    hpcom:book_status hpcom:book-read ;
    hpcom:date_book_read "2023-06-11T06:00:00"^^xsd:dateTime ;
    schema:aggregatedRating hptag:Rating3 ;
    schema:author "John Brunner" ;
    schema:dateCreated "1968"^^xsd:int ;
    schema:genre hpcom:BookFiction,
        hpcom:BookSciFi ;
    schema:name "Stand on Zanzibar" ;
    schema:review "This book is famous for being written in the 60s and 'predicting' a lot of the modern technologies that we have today. It certainly contains several of these to be impressive. The writing style is confusing (quite 60s) for today, and the plot is the typical geopolitical situation. Interesting book to read for a cult classic. A movie on this made in the 70s would have been quite cool to see today."@en ;
    schema:url "https://harshp.com/hobbies/books/629"^^xsd:anyURI .

book:63 a hpcom:Book,
        hpcom:BookReading,
        hpcom:RenderedItem,
        schema:Book ;
    hpcom:book_id hpcom:63 ;
    hpcom:book_owned_medium hpcom:PhysicalBook ;
    hpcom:book_read_medium hpcom:PhysicalBook ;
    hpcom:book_status hpcom:book-read ;
    hpcom:date_book_read "2023-08-18T00:00:00"^^xsd:dateTime ;
    schema:aggregatedRating hptag:Rating4 ;
    schema:author "Charles Bukowski" ;
    schema:dateCreated "1982"^^xsd:int ;
    schema:genre hpcom:BookFiction ;
    schema:isPartOf list:cork ;
    schema:name "Ham on Rye" ;
    schema:review "Bukowski has a style. An ugly degraded style. But that's also what we avoid thinking we look like in the mirror. In this case, Bukowski writes about childhood and how messed up growing typically is. I really liked reading this book, and seeing how the adult Henry Chinaski emerged from the younger version."@en ;
    schema:url "https://harshp.com/hobbies/books/63"^^xsd:anyURI .

book:630 a hpcom:Book,
        hpcom:BookReading,
        hpcom:RenderedItem,
        schema:Book ;
    hpcom:book_id hpcom:630 ;
    hpcom:book_owned_medium hpcom:EBook ;
    hpcom:book_read_medium hpcom:EBook ;
    hpcom:book_status hpcom:book-read ;
    hpcom:date_book_read "2024-06-10T00:00:00"^^xsd:dateTime ;
    schema:aggregatedRating hptag:Rating3 ;
    schema:author "Cory Doctorow" ;
    schema:dateCreated "2020"^^xsd:int ;
    schema:genre hpcom:BookFiction,
        hpcom:BookSciFi ;
    schema:name "Attack Surface" ;
    schema:review "Novelisation of American authoritarian dystopia where people use tech to degrade democracy and force people to do stuff. Based on the real world - in the sense that things are not far fetched and probably closer to what happens. Story was okay. Tech stuff was okay - a bit overexposed but still fit the story. Its depressing to read this and think that's how the world functions."@en ;
    schema:url "https://harshp.com/hobbies/books/630"^^xsd:anyURI .

