    schema:dateCreated "2020"^^xsd:int ;
    schema:genre hpcom:BookNonFiction ;
    schema:name "How to Destroy Surveillance Capitalism" ;
    schema:review "Brought this because I wanted to support Doctorow and hear more of what he says. The book itself is quite short, and the 'chatpers' are more like a short commentary in between things. The premise of the book sounds explosive, but the actual contents are more of a primer to the situation rather than a primer to an explosion. Still, I made notes of several sentences which I thought were good to use when describing the things in articles or to others. So there was value in reading more of the same."@en ;
    schema:url "https://harshp.com/hobbies/books/896"^^xsd:anyURI .

