    schema:dateCreated "2023"^^xsd:int ;
    schema:genre hpcom:BookFiction ;
    schema:isPartOf list:DCU ;
    schema:name "The Lost Bookshop" ;
    schema:review "Picked this up because I like books, ergo I like bookshops, and 'book hunting' is something that resonates with me. The story is about a lost bookshop and how it shapes the lives of three characters. Its set in Dublin, featuring someone who is doing a PhD, there's mention of Trinity and Ha'Penny and other local areas - so of course I picked it up and gave it a go. Was an okay book, enjoyable as a sort of sheepish TV movie that I wouldn't otherwise go for. The bibliophilia is what enticed me."@en ;
    schema:url "https://harshp.com/hobbies/books/915"^^xsd:anyURI .

