        hpcom:BookSciFi ;
    schema:name "The Lost Cause" ;
    schema:review "I didn't know this book was YA (Young Adult), so while reading it I constantly kept being annoyed by the language and the juvenile characters. When I found out, I changed my perspective about. Overall, its a good optimistic story set in a rough time, where the government has got its bearings on correct, and everything is green and clean. Still, not a great book. Might have been interesting when I was younger and not as matured."@en ;
