    schema:aggregatedRating hptag:Rating3 ;
    schema:author "Andrea Komlosy" ;
    schema:dateCreated "2014"^^xsd:int ;
    schema:genre hpcom:BookNonFiction ;
    schema:name "Work: The Last 1,000 Years" ;
    schema:review "An ambitious premise as the book summarises the different of 'work' over the last thousand years. The earlier era seems a bit vague as to how we know about these things, but the book provides ample references (I didn't check them though). The later years cover more familiar things. I was excited to see how all these things connect to the modern practices. But alas the book stops just short of modern day work. A lost opportunity. The book's value and novelty is merely as a historical informatica."@en ;
    schema:url "https://harshp.com/hobbies/books/919"^^xsd:anyURI .

