    schema:dateCreated "2024"^^xsd:int ;
    schema:genre hpcom:BookNonFiction ;
    schema:name "Data Grab: The New Colonialism of Big Tech and How to Fight Back" ;
    schema:review "The book might be a more gentler introduction for people who don't know what has been happening with the capitalist tech industry filled to the brim with surveillance advertising. But otherwise it was a lot of repeated narratives and information. What was interesting at the start was the promise of solutions - but they were far too simplified and not explored in detail at all."@en ;
