    schema:name "Vulture Capitalism: Corporate Crimes, Backdoor Bailouts and the Death of Freedom" ;
    schema:review "A powerful book that gives a succint history lesson on corporate economics and how things keep getting screwed and we keep making the same mistakes again and again with every decade. This book is a good resource to understand the economic side of economy and how certain economic philosophies shaped what we have come to make of the modern world."@en ;
