book:987 a hpcom:Book,
        hpcom:BookReading,
        hpcom:RenderedItem,
        schema:Book ;
    hpcom:book_id hpcom:987 ;
    hpcom:book_owned_medium hpcom:EBook ;
    hpcom:book_read_medium hpcom:EBook ;
    hpcom:book_status hpcom:book-read ;
    hpcom:date_book_read "2025-09-11T00:00:00"^^xsd:dateTime ;
    schema:aggregatedRating hptag:Rating4 ;
    schema:author "James S. A. Corey" ;
    schema:dateCreated "2015"^^xsd:int ;
    schema:genre hpcom:BookFiction,
        hpcom:BookSciFi ;
    schema:name "Nemesis Games" ;
    schema:review "Book 5: The Gang goes their separate ways and then shit happens that makes them want to get back together. I liked that this wasn't another episodic instance of the same stuff and that each character got enough of a back and individual story to have them be relevant in the larger story. I thought the pieces on Earth were a little slow and/or a little low in terms of having content. I'd have liked to see more, but that's the part where the good styorytelling comes through. Having less and wanting more is good if the overall story still is enjoying, which this was. Onwards to the next book."@en ;
    schema:url "https://harshp.com/hobbies/books/987"^^xsd:anyURI .

book:988 a hpcom:Book,
        hpcom:BookReading,
        hpcom:RenderedItem,
        schema:Book ;
    hpcom:book_id hpcom:988 ;
    hpcom:book_owned_medium hpcom:EBook ;
    hpcom:book_read_medium hpcom:EBook ;
    hpcom:book_status hpcom:book-read ;
    hpcom:date_book_read "2025-09-21T00:00:00"^^xsd:dateTime ;
    schema:aggregatedRating hptag:Rating4 ;
    schema:author "James S. A. Corey" ;
    schema:dateCreated "2016"^^xsd:int ;
    schema:genre hpcom:BookFiction,
        hpcom:BookSciFi ;
    schema:name "Babylon's Ashes" ;
    schema:review "Book 6: I've got to hand it to the authors. They know how to keep things interesting and adding more and more chaos and layers to the story. This one is about conflicts between factions and idealogies and it all plays out in the system. Good stuff, entertaining stuff. But at no point did it feel like this is a book on its own, so I kept expecting more things to happen or be clear, and then at one point I realised that it isn't in this book and that I would have to read one. Okay, next one it is."@en ;
    schema:url "https://harshp.com/hobbies/books/988"^^xsd:anyURI .

